Java OOP and Exception Handling Apps
Description
This project contains multiple small Java applications that demonstrate object-oriented programming and exception handling.

Mechanic and Employee System
•	Models a workplace with different types of employees and vehicles.
•	Demonstrates OOP concepts such as inheritance, encapsulation, and polymorphism.
•	Main class: MechanicApp.java

Password Validation
•	Validates user-entered passwords.
•	Uses a custom exception (PasswordVerifyException.java) to enforce rules.
•	Main class: PasswordValidationApp.java

Division Application
•	Performs division between numbers.
•	Handles exceptions such as division by zero.
•	Main class: DivisionApp.java

Requirements
•	Java Development Kit (JDK) 17 or higher
•	IntelliJ IDEA (Community or Ultimate Edition)

Running in IntelliJ IDEA
1.	Open IntelliJ IDEA.
o	Go to File > New > Project from Existing Sources...
o	Select the folder containing these .java files.

2.	Configure the JDK.
o	When prompted, select Java SDK 17 or higher.

3.	Mark the source folder.
o	Right-click the folder with your .java files → Mark Directory as > Sources Root.

4.	Run the desired application.
o	Open MechanicApp.java, PasswordValidationApp.java, or DivisionApp.java.
o	Right-click inside the editor → Run 'ClassName.main()'.

